Languages
=========

Player languages are independent of race, although some player races are
accorded extra languages. Languages are specified in the language.h header.

A living's language knowledge is either fluent, or non-fluent (regular).
At the moment, the distinction only affects whether the say command shows
an accent or not. There is also a default language and a native language
for each living as well. The default language is the languages used with the
'say' command, and the native language is used by 'rsay'.

Adding new languages
--------------------
To add a language, alter language.h to include the new language in the
ALL_LANGUAGES array, and assign a color to it in LCOLOR.

Giving language knowledge
-------------------------
    void add_language(string)
    void add_fluent_language(string)
        Both of these functions give appropriate knowledge of a language.
        They can also be passed arrays of languages as well.
    void set_default_language(string)
    void set_native_language(string)
        These functions set the say and rsay default languages.
    void remove_language(string)
        Removes all knowledge of a language.

Checking language knowledge
---------------------------
    string query_native_language()
    string query_default_language()
        These return the appropriate language setting.
    status query_language(string)
    status query_fluent_language(string)
        These return 1 if the language is known.

